Taiwan proposes T $ 10 bln airport town - paper . A Taiwan cabinet panel has proposed building a T $ 10 billion airport town in the nothern county of Taoyuan , the China Times Express evening newspaper said on Sunday . The town would be completed in June 2000 , the paper said . It will be built around the CKS international airport . The northern part would comprise an air cargo zone , while the southern area would be for passenger airline - related service industries . It would also have commercial , administration , entertainment and residential areas to house 36 , 000 people . The proposal needs final approval by the full cabinet . The newspaper gave no further details . - - Taipei Newsroom ( 5080815 ) 
